SIMPLE: melting
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melting
<hw>Melt"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Liquefaction; the act of causing
(something) to melt, or the process of becoming melted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Melting point</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>the
degree of temperature at which a solid substance melts or fuses; <as>as,
the <ex>melting point</ex> of ice is 0⟦deg⟧ Centigrade or 32⟦deg⟧ Fahr.,
that of urea is 132⟦deg⟧ Centigrade</as>. Pressure affects the melting
point somewhat, and if not specified the melting point is usually taken
to be at atmospheric pressure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melting</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Melting
<hw>Melt"ing</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Causing to melt; becoming melted;
-- used literally or figuratively; <as>as, a <ex>melting</ex> heat; a
<ex>melting</ex> appeal; a <ex>melting</ex> mood</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Melt"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melting pot</ent>⟦br⟧
